                            <comment id="13939011" author="tmueller" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2014 09:45:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In this issue, I would just fix the build. Refactoring the tests is not urgent and can be done later, I opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1556&quot; title=&quot;Document and test additional BlobStore contracts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-1556&quot;&gt;OAK-1556&lt;/a&gt; for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13947736" author="chetanm" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2014 09:46:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Discussed this with Thomas. BlobStore design has a feature where you can combine blocks by combining there id and testEmptyIdentifier checks for that. This feature is currently not part of the contract of BlobStore and is kind of implementation detail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As it does not make sense for DataStore based BlobStore I have ignored this test in MongoDataStoreBlobStoreTest &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1581768&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1581768&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
